## Scenario 1 — New User

1. User lands on homepage — hero with input + research type selector visible immediately
2. Below hero: "How it works" — three steps explaining Analyst, Critic, output structure
3. Below that: tabbed demo researches by type — user clicks tab matching their interest, reads full output including Critic challenge, cost breakdown visible
4. User types own question, selects research type, hits "Run research"
5. Email gate appears inline: "Enter your email to run this research free"
6. Magic link sent → user clicks in same tab → run starts immediately
7. Results load: dimensions, scores, evidence blocks, Critic challenge
8. Results page footer: "API cost: $0.43 · Service fee 30%: $0.13 · You paid: $0.00 (free run) · Future runs from $0.56"
9. Countdown visible below results: "This research is stored for 47h 23m. Top up to save it permanently."
10. User tries to export → "Export requires balance. Top up to continue."
11. Top-up screen: 3 USD-priced packs + BYOK option with copy: "Use your own API key — your data goes directly to the model provider, never through our servers"
12. Stripe Checkout → returns to tab → balance shown in header as "$4.50 remaining"
13. Research saved permanently, export unlocked → user downloads JSON + Markdown
14. User runs second research → balance decrements in real-time, shown in header

