## Scenario 3 — Shared Research + Collaborative Challenge

1. Owner selects one or more researches from their list, clicks "Share"
2. Share link generated — one link regardless of how many researches selected
3. Owner pastes link into Slack (or email, WhatsApp — tool doesn't care)
4. **Marcus** opens link — no account prompt, full research visible
5. If multiple researches shared: list view shows each research with dimension score summary row — Marcus clicks into whichever interests him
6. Banner at top: "This link expires in 47h · Sign up to keep access" and "Run your own research — first one's free"
7. Marcus comments on a specific dimension → text field opens → comment appears inline flagged as "External reviewer"
8. **Priya** opens same link on phone — mobile layout, sees Marcus's comment, adds reply nested inline
9. **Owner** receives email notification: "2 new comments on your shared research"
10. Owner opens research from their list — sees all comments inline, replies
11. **Marcus** clicks "Sign up to keep access" → email → magic link → account created
12. Shared research now permanently accessible to Marcus — no expiry, appears in his "Shared with me" list
13. Marcus sees CTA: "Run your own research — first one's free" → runs research → becomes user
14. **Priya** doesn't sign up → access expires after 48hr → sees "Sign up to keep access" on next visit
15. Owner can see in share management: who has account access vs. link-only access, can revoke per person or per research anytime
